ebra","topic":"Algebraic manipulation","qtype":"algebraic manipulation","g":"mixed","src":"0580/11/M/J/18 Q22","year":2018,"session":"MayJune","tex":"Factorise completely.\n\n(a) $10 + 16w$\n\n(b) $12tx - 8t^2$","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":1},{"label":"(b)","marks":2}],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"recall","cmd":"simplify"},{"id":"0580-2018MayJune-Paper11-Q23","paper":"2018MayJune-Paper11","qnum":23,"marks":3,"topics":["Number"],"s":"1.4","d":1,"cat":"number","topic":"Fractions, decimals, percentages","qtype":"fractions, decimals, percentages","g":"mixed","src":"0580/11/M/J/18 Q23","year":2018,"session":"MayJune","tex":"Without using your calculator, work out $\\dfrac{1}{4} \\div \\dfrac{6}{35}$.\nYou must show all your working and give your answer as a fraction in its simplest form.","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate"},{"id":"0580-2018MayJune-Paper11-Q24","paper":"2018MayJune-Paper11","qnum":24,"marks":4,"topics":["Algebra and graphs"],"s":"2.5","d":1,"cat":"algebra","topic":"Equations","qtype":"equations","g":"mixed","src":"0580/11/M/J/18 Q24","year":2018,"session":"MayJune","tex":"Solve the simultaneous equations.\nYou must show all your working.\n\n3x + 10y = 106\n5x - 4y = 1\n\nx = \ny =","parts":[],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"solve"},{"id":"0580-2018MayJune-Paper11-Q25","paper":"2018MayJune-Paper11","qnum":25,"marks":6,"topics":["Geometry","Mensuration","Statistics"],"s":"4.6","d":1,"cat":"geometry","topic":"Angles","qtype":"angle calculations","g":"mixed","src":"0580/11/M/J/18 Q25","year":2018,"session":"MayJune","tex":"40 people were asked how many times they visited the cinema in one month.\nThe table shows the results.\n\n\\begin{tabular}{|c|c|c|c|c|c|c|c|c|}\n\\hline\nNumber of cinema visits & 0 & 1 & 2 & 3 & 4 & 5 & 6 & 7 \\\\\n\\hline\nFrequency & 5 & 5 & 6 & 6 & 7 & 3 & 6 & 2 \\\\\n\\hline\n\\end{tabular}\n\n(a) (i) (b) Find the mode.\n\n(c) Calculate the mean.\n\n(d) Omar wants to show the information from the table in a pie chart.\nCalculate the sector angle for the people who visited the cinema 5 times.","parts":[{"label":"(a)","marks":0},{"label":"(b)","marks":1},{"label":"(c)","marks":3},{"label":"(d)","marks":2}],"hasFigure":false,"cognitive":"apply","cmd":"calculate","texHtml":"40 people were asked how many times they visited the cinema in one month.\nThe table shows the results.\n\n<div class=\"pp-table-wrap\"><table class=\"pp-table\"><tr><th style=\"text-align:center\">Number of cinema visits</th><th style=\"text-align:center\">0</th><th style=\"text-align:center\">1</th><th style=\"text-align:center\">2</th><th style=\"text-align:center\">3</th><th style=\"text-align:center\">4</th><th style=\"text-align:center\">5</th><th style=\"text-align:center\">6</th><th style=\"text-align:center\">7</th></tr><tr><td style=\"text-align:center\">Frequency</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">5</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">5</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">6</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">6</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">7</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">3</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">6</td><td style=\"text-align:center\">2</td></tr></table></div>\n\n(a) (i) (b) Find the mode.\n\n(c) Calculate the mean.\n\n(d) Omar wants to show the information from the table in a pie chart.\nCalculate the sector angle for the people who visited the cinema 5 times."}]